problem:
Find the ordered pair $(x,y)$ if

\begin{align*}
x+y&=(5-x)+(5-y),\\
x-y&=(x-1)+(y-1).
\end{align*}

Find the ordered pair $(x,y)$ if

\begin{align*}
x+y&=(5-x)+(5-y),\\
x-y&=(x-1)+(y-1).
\end{align*}

Find the ordered pair $(x,y)$ if

\begin{align*}
x+y&=(5-x)+(5-y),\\
x-y&=(x-1)+(y-1).
\end{align*}

Find the ordered pair $(x,y)$ if

\begin{align*}
x+y&=(5-x)+(5-y),\\
x-y&=(x-1)+(y-1).
\end{align*}

Find the ordered pair $(x,y)$ if

\begin{align*}
x+y&=(5-x)+(5-y),\\
x-y&=(x-1)+(y-1).
\end{align*}

Find the ordered pair $(x,y)$ if

\begin{align*}
x+y&=(5-x)+(5-y),\\
x-y&=(x-1)+(y-1).
\end{align*}

Find the ordered pair $(x,y)$ if

\begin{align*}
x+y&=(5-x)+(5-y),\\
x-y&=(x-1)+(y-1).
\end{align*}

Find the ordered pair $(x,y)$ if

\begin{align*}
x+y&=(5-x)+(5-y),\\
x-y&=(x-1)+(y-1).
\end{align*}

